g.text: "I don't. Mail the letter and let's be done with this."
Empathy: Dodged the bullet there... He must see the box as the weaker of the two, and you as a bully -- something he doesn't stand for.
Pain Threshold: Your toe has suffered damage. It hurts!
You: I feel you, mail collection box.
Mail Collection Box: The mail collection box seems cathartic, thankful even. So do you. You shudder. Then you swallow.
You: "Oh, you're being sarcastic. I get it. It was actually a dick move."
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant pats the box, ever so slightly.
Empathy: He must see the box as the weaker of the two, and you as a bully -- something he doesn't stand for.
Mail Collection Box: Other than kicking? You were right!
Kim Kitsuragi: "It's not going to be that easy. We need to dirty our hands with the signatures." He looks around. "I assume that's the goal here."
Mail Collection Box: You drop the white envelope in the darkness. It lands with a soft thud on what sounds like a couple of letters.
Perception (Hearing): About a week's worth of mail has collected in there. They'll empty this very soon.
Mail Collection Box: The mail collection box has no faith in your psychopathic manipulations.
Mail Collection Box: The box seems happy.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Alright, let's go back to Evrart." The lieutenant turns towards the industrial harbour. "If we don't mention anything to him, he won't know before it's too late."
You: Drop the white envelope into the mailbox.
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant pats the box on the head, ever so slightly, before walking away.
You: Drop the white envelope into the mailbox.
Mail Collection Box: Other than developing a personal relationship? Looks like you were right.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Let's go back to Evrart." The lieutenant turns towards the industrial harbour. "This better be worth it -- after what we did."
You: Drop the white envelope into the mailbox.
Mail Collection Box: The mail collection box has no faith in your psychopathic manipulations.
Mail Collection Box: The box seems happy.
Inland Empire: For good or ill, the deed is done.
You: "Good mail delivery box." (Pat the box.)
You: Mail collection box, you should man the fuck up.
Mail Collection Box: The mailbox does not know how to man up, it is an inanimate object.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Cool." The lieutenant nods approvingly. "You really showed that mail collection box."
Mail Collection Box: The dented yellow mailbox greets you with it's graffito and bullet holes in the front.
You: "Fuck you, mail delivery box!" (Kick it.)
You: Been there, *Poste L'Aventurier* mail collection box... been there.
Mail Collection Box: The dented yellow mailbox greets you with it's graffito, bullet holes and an RCM sticker.
Perception (Sight): A faint sticker on the side reads: "RCM Emergencies Desk no 8-100-2", with a slogan: "Mankind, be vigilant!"
Perception (Sight): "Eat shit, pig!", "FUCKED BY THE CUNN" and "Saint-G" with a crown have been scribbled on it. "Jennie is a WHORE" and "*Baise cette* mailbox!" also.
Mail Collection Box: There is a hollow ring as you kick the box. It sounds like it's mostly empty. Your toe hurts now.
Mail Collection Box: There is a hollow, saddened ring as you kick the L'Aventurier mail collection box. It sounds betrayed, in disbelief even.
You: Drop the white envelope into the mailbox.
Mail Collection Box: But the documents inside the envelope still lack the required signatures...
Mail Collection Box: This "Poste L'Aventurier" mail collection box has been heavily vandalized with graffito. A closer inspection reveals two bullet holes in the front.
Rhetoric: He does not actually think it's cool. If anything, the lieutenant feels sorry for the poor box -- he's leaning in to inspect the layers of graffito that deface it.
You: (Rub your toe.) "You think so? You think it was cool?"
Logic: It's not going to be that easy. Evrart wants you to dirty your hands getting these signatures and he will quickly find out if you just mail.
You: "I knew we'd get to use this mailbox -- for something."
I knew I'd get to use this mailbox -- for something.
Mail Collection Box: There is a hollow ring as you kick the box. It sounds like it's mostly empty. Your toe hurts now.
Shivers: And then suddenly you see it: over all the other graffitos someone has -- using the tip of a very sharp knife -- cut the words: REVACHOL FOREVER.
Mail Collection Box: There is a hollow, saddened ring as you kick the L'Aventurier mail collection box. It sounds betrayed, in disbelief even.
Logic: Probably did the right thing. You can't trust that slug Evrart -- you *know* he's going to play you somehow.
